At the demonstrations, protesters chanted for Morrison to step down, for an increase in fire service funding, and for drastic action on climate change.
Follow up protests of several thousand took place in major capital cities again in the week after.
These small-scale work stoppages should be escalated into a national strike of workers and students to demand immediate funding for fire services and action on climate change.
A mass strike and protests to shut down the economy for even one day would put immense pressure on the government.
